1
00:00:01,033 --> 00:00:06,600
(Episode 5: As Long As I Love You)

2
00:00:08,439 --> 00:00:11,100
I've never made scrambled eggs
for a baby before.

3
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:13,733
Look at that.

4
00:00:13,758 --> 00:00:14,808
(Breakfast not done yet)

5
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,000
It's egg porridge.

6
00:00:16,366 --> 00:00:17,433
Are you sure this is okay?

7
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,700
It doesn't look great now,

8
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:20,754
but it'll turn out just right soon.

9
00:00:20,866 --> 00:00:22,200
(The spectators leave.)

10
00:00:23,856 --> 00:00:24,591
Okay.

11
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,600
(I'll just play with toys.)

12
00:00:28,966 --> 00:00:31,566
(Finally, Yu Jun takes interest
in the paper blocks.)

13
00:00:31,566 --> 00:00:32,333
Yu Jun.

14
00:00:34,566 --> 00:00:35,466
That's it.

15
00:00:35,466 --> 00:00:37,666
(He accidentally succeeds
in knocking down the dominoes.)

16
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:39,806
I told you it would turn out fine.

17
00:00:40,766 --> 00:00:42,100
I told you.

18
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,466
(The eggs actually turned out okay.)

19
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:45,200
I'm such a good cook.

20
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,816
Yu Jun, let's do the shark.

21
00:00:51,541 --> 00:00:53,641
This needs to cool down
a lot more than you'd think.

22
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,556
I know. I'm letting it sit for a bit.

23
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,333
I hope Yu Jun likes this.

24
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:00,966
(Yu Jun's baby food has
finally been plated.)

25
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:02,166
Yu Jun.

26
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:05,633
Give me a hug.

27
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:06,766
(Hug fee: Prepaid in food)
Mommy?

28
00:01:08,066 --> 00:01:09,866
Yu Jun, it's me, YEONJUN.

29
00:01:09,866 --> 00:01:10,633
YEONJUN.

30
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:11,799
(YEONJUN's affection only grew
after a day apart.)

31
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,666
That's right. It's me, YEONJUN.

32
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:18,933
(Yu Jun finally gives YEONJUN a hug.)

33
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:22,466
(Persistence finally pays off.)

34
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,066
(Is YEONJUN's unrequited love
finally over?)

35
00:01:25,066 --> 00:01:25,953
Mommy?

36
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:27,187
Did you say YEONJUN?

37
00:01:28,066 --> 00:01:30,800
(Still a bit awkward at holding the baby)

38
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:34,333
(While YEONJUN holds his unrequited love,)

39
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:35,433
Do you want to get down?

40
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:37,133
(SOOBIN blows on the food
to cool it down.)

41
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:39,773
- Nom-nom.
- Huh?

42
00:01:39,797 --> 00:01:41,868
Nom-nom.

43
00:01:41,868 --> 00:01:43,708
(Ready to eat with his bib on)

44
00:01:43,733 --> 00:01:44,800
That's it.

45
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,866
What a good boy.

46
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,776
- How is it? Is it cool enough now?
- I think it's fine.

47
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:51,866
It's not hot at all.

48
00:01:51,866 --> 00:01:54,100
(They've become pros
at handling baby food.)

49
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,900
(It's finally Yu Jun's breakfast time.)

50
00:01:58,233 --> 00:01:59,300
Give Yu Jun a spoon to hold.

51
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,866
And use the other one to feed him.

52
00:02:00,866 --> 00:02:02,866
He likes holding one himself.

53
00:02:02,866 --> 00:02:03,766
Really?

54
00:02:03,766 --> 00:02:05,033
(SOOBIN shares a parenting tip.)

55
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:09,000
(A bite for you)

56
00:02:09,366 --> 00:02:10,866
Are you feeding the uncles again?

57
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:12,466
Did you just feed me?

58
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:13,533
Why are you sniffing your hand?

59
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:14,933
(Shh)

60
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:16,700
Let's eat now.

61
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,733
- That's it. Good boy.
- Well done.

62
00:02:22,033 --> 00:02:22,933
Open up.

63
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,166
That's it.

64
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:27,300
- Does he like it?
- Yes.

65
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,333
He loves it.

66
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:30,333
(They're happy
seeing Yu Jun enjoy his food.)

67
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,633
Here we go.

68
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,166
Nom-nom.

69
00:02:33,466 --> 00:02:35,100
Great. You're a good eater.

70
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:35,933
So cute.

71
00:02:35,958 --> 00:02:37,058
(Shimmies)

72
00:02:37,466 --> 00:02:38,400
You like it, don't you?

73
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,108
(It got on my hand. Wipe it, please.)

74
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,066
Do you want me to wipe it off?

75
00:02:41,066 --> 00:02:43,600
(Complimentary hand-wiping service)

76
00:02:44,866 --> 00:02:46,900
That's good.

77
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:47,833
(He can eat by himself.)

78
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,833
He loves food so much.

79
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:50,733
He really does.

80
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:52,000
He's grown so much.

81
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,333
He enjoyed his meal last time too.

82
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:54,800
- How cute.
- So cute.

83
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,933
(Look at Yu Jun go! He's a natural!)

84
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:58,266
Good boy.

85
00:02:58,266 --> 00:03:00,047
You've grown enough to eat by yourself.

86
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:02,833
I'm so happy you enjoy your food.

87
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:03,700
Yu Jun.

88
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,633
(You focus on the food.
I'll focus on the mess.)

89
00:03:06,366 --> 00:03:07,466
Nom-nom.

90
00:03:07,466 --> 00:03:08,866
That's it.

91
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:10,600
He loves it.

92
00:03:11,466 --> 00:03:12,726
You're already opening your mouth?

93
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,133
How adorable.

94
00:03:14,766 --> 00:03:16,733
(Feeling full just from watching him eat)

95
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:17,566
So smart.

96
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:19,366
What a good boy.

97
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:20,900
(Looking at Yu Jun with pure adoration)

98
00:03:21,266 --> 00:03:22,566
Okay.

99
00:03:22,566 --> 00:03:24,666
I think Yu Jun likes trying new flavors.

100
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:28,466
He likes a little cheese too.

101
00:03:28,466 --> 00:03:29,500
Does he?

102
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,600
I'll mix some into your meal.

103
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,833
Let me add a little more flavor.

104
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,700
(YEONJUN tries feeding him food
topped with cheese.)

105
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,600
(Picking out only the cheese)

106
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,200
He likes eating just the cheese.

107
00:03:39,066 --> 00:03:40,033
(He copies the way YEONJUN laughs.)

108
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,166
Yu Jun!

109
00:03:42,166 --> 00:03:44,166
(I love cheese!)

110
00:03:44,166 --> 00:03:45,566
Good job.

111
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:48,500
(No, I want cheese.)

112
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,533
- No. Finish your meal first.
- Finish your meal first.

113
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:52,533
- That's dessert.
- Dessert.

114
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:53,633
(Better listen to Mommy.)

115
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,733
(Dessert tastes even better
during the meal.)

116
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,633
I'll give you cheese after this.

117
00:03:58,033 --> 00:03:58,866
Do you want water?

118
00:03:58,866 --> 00:04:00,766
(He communicates surprisingly well
with his babbling.)

119
00:04:02,066 --> 00:04:04,533
(Drinking)

120
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:11,700
(Yu Jun's specialty:
chugging water in one go)

121
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,200
(Done.)

122
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:15,566
Are you done?

123
00:04:15,566 --> 00:04:17,633
(His breakfast is over.)

124
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,266
I'll clean up.

125
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:21,766
Yu Jun, give me your hands.

126
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,233
You've got food everywhere.

127
00:04:27,266 --> 00:04:30,800
(Meticulous)

128
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:34,166
(While he's at it,
he washes the baby's face too.)

129
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:41,433
(Then he wipes down the table.)

130
00:04:41,966 --> 00:04:45,933
(He cleans every corner
without missing a spot.)

131
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:49,266
(Making noise)

132
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,866
(Making the same noise)

133
00:04:50,866 --> 00:04:52,966
(Shaking his head)

134
00:04:53,366 --> 00:04:57,400
(Yu Jun and YEONJUN's dance time)

135
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,266
There you go.

136
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:07,033
(After putting Yu Jun down,
he seriously begins cleaning the chair.)

137
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:12,666
(Cleaning and cleaning)

138
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,333
(You're going to wear the chair out
at this rate.)

139
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:21,033
(Is it finally over?)

140
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:23,566
(Nope. It's only the beginning)

141
00:05:23,566 --> 00:05:26,100
(He takes cleaning very seriously.)

142
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,500
(YEONJUN sees cleaning opportunities
everywhere.)

143
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:34,100
(He even cleans up the mess
he made himself.)

144
00:05:34,766 --> 00:05:39,466
(Leave no trace behind.)

145
00:05:39,966 --> 00:05:40,800
Yu Jun.

146
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,400
Come here.

147
00:05:42,966 --> 00:05:45,566
(Where am I going?)

148
00:05:45,566 --> 00:05:48,100
(He's back at the kitchen table.)

149
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,533
Let's brush your teeth.

150
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:50,600
(It's time for Yu Jun to brush his teeth.)

151
00:05:50,966 --> 00:05:52,600
Do you want to try, or should I do it?

152
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,633
- I don't think I can.
- I'm not sure I can.

153
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:56,600
You should try first. I'll try after that.

154
00:05:57,366 --> 00:05:58,466
(Squeezing out the toothpaste)

155
00:05:58,466 --> 00:06:00,166
Is this too little?

156
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,266
(He's ready.)

157
00:06:03,266 --> 00:06:04,466
It's all over your face.

158
00:06:04,466 --> 00:06:05,533
(Enough with the wiping)

159
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:06,600
You want me to stop? Okay.

160
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,966
Open up, Yu Jun.

161
00:06:09,966 --> 00:06:11,766
(No.)

162
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,766
Say, "Ah."

163
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,833
(Let me down.)

164
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,733
- Open up. Good boy.
- Good boy.

165
00:06:17,733 --> 00:06:18,633
(It's not as easy as expected.)

166
00:06:19,666 --> 00:06:20,666
Say, "Ah."

167
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,833
You don't want to?

168
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:23,800
Come on.

169
00:06:24,466 --> 00:06:25,300
Hold on.

170
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:27,600
Is it because I held him like this?

171
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:28,966
Yu Jun.
(Where did SOOBIN go?)

172
00:06:30,966 --> 00:06:32,700
(Bumping heads)

173
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,133
(SOOBIN returns with rice crackers.)

174
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:37,466
Yu Jun, say, "Ah."

175
00:06:37,466 --> 00:06:38,333
Yu Jun.

176
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,333
Yu Jun.

177
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,666
Open up.

178
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:43,366
(He finally manages to get the toothbrush
into his mouth using the rice cracker.)

179
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,500
(I only want the rice cracker.)

180
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:48,166
- Hold on.
- That's strange.

181
00:06:48,166 --> 00:06:49,466
(Let's try again.)

182
00:06:49,466 --> 00:06:51,966
Let's try one more time.

183
00:06:51,966 --> 00:06:54,447
I think it's because I'm holding him.

184
00:06:54,739 --> 00:06:56,249
Maybe he'll be fine if I let it go?

185
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,400
Please try.

186
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,733
This is my one wish for the year.

187
00:07:01,033 --> 00:07:02,266
Good boy.

188
00:07:02,266 --> 00:07:03,200
- Yu Jun, here.
- Please.

189
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,233
It's my biggest wish of the year.

190
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,826
Please open your mouth just this once.

191
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,333
I'm not just doing this for fun.

192
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,100
But you need to brush your teeth.

193
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:16,666
- Okay. Don't cry. Please.
- Don't cry. I got it.

194
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:18,533
Give it to me. I'll try.

195
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,233
Open up.

196
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:24,966
(It was too easy.)

197
00:07:24,966 --> 00:07:26,666
Well done!

198
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,133
Good job, Yu Jun.

199
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:30,533
(Let's try one more time.)

200
00:07:32,266 --> 00:07:34,133
(That's enough.)

201
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:35,733
(You can go now.)

202
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,400
(A 15-month-old disarms the 27-year-old.)

203
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,500
Hey, come on.

204
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,933
(It's mine now.)

205
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:41,866
Wait.

206
00:07:43,133 --> 00:07:44,000
Hold on.
(He manages to get the toothbrush back.)

207
00:07:45,033 --> 00:07:46,033
Show me your teeth.

208
00:07:47,566 --> 00:07:51,266
(Yu Jun has only been cooperative
with YEONJUN today.)

209
00:07:52,866 --> 00:07:53,866
(The unexpected tooth-brushing expert)

210
00:07:53,866 --> 00:07:55,300
That's it.

211
00:07:56,466 --> 00:07:57,510
(It's over now.)

212
00:07:57,544 --> 00:07:58,875
The inside is not done yet.

213
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:01,300
(Let's call that a success.)

214
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,333
(Get me out of here.)

215
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,133
You want to get out?

216
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:07,800
(Put me down.)

217
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,233
That's it!

218
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:15,600
That was it.

219
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,600
He listens to us so well.

220
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:21,133
Yu Jun, you wear size XL?

221
00:08:21,966 --> 00:08:24,800
(Baby Yu Jun is a big boy!
He's already in XL.)

222
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,633
- So cool.
- Just in case.

223
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:28,333
You wear XL already!

224
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:32,333
(It's time for a diaper change.)

225
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,000
(Sneaking a peek at the baby's butt)

226
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:36,266
Hold on. Where are you going?

227
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:38,600
Yu Jun, this is so embarrassing for you!

228
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,187
When you grow up and watch this,
you'll probably be embarrassed.

229
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:45,000
Yu Jun.

230
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,500
Give me five.

231
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:47,300
Yu Jun.

232
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,200
No.

233
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,633
(He gets caught in the end.)

234
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:53,833
Let's get changed.

235
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,833
(Let me go.)

236
00:08:56,266 --> 00:08:59,600
He's about to cry.
Fly him around like an airplane.

237
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,933
(A flight is the cure for crying.)

238
00:09:03,066 --> 00:09:06,166
(The airplane is flying a bit too low.)

239
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:07,566
How exciting.

240
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,533
(Sighing)

241
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,533
You're winded already?

242
00:09:13,766 --> 00:09:14,566
We're done.

243
00:09:14,566 --> 00:09:16,266
Just lifting him up while sitting down...

244
00:09:16,266 --> 00:09:17,566
(Mission accomplished
despite the physical toll)

245
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:20,066
Okay.

246
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,166
Okay. Yu Jun!

247
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,433
(Putting Yu Jun's pants on is
YEONJUN's job.)

248
00:09:24,066 --> 00:09:26,033
(Pouty lips)

249
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,033
Give me your arms.

250
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,733
We're done.

251
00:09:29,733 --> 00:09:30,966
All set.

252
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,633
Yes! We did it.

253
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:34,500
You did it so well.

254
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:38,133
(You did a great job getting changed.)

255
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:39,733
- Let's go out.
- Let's go.

256
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,366
Let's go outside.

257
00:09:42,766 --> 00:09:43,866
Guess where we're going.

258
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,166
Yu Jun.

259
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:48,100
Guess where we're going.

260
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:50,523
He's not even looking.

261
00:09:51,366 --> 00:09:52,300
He's looking out, isn't he?

262
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,533
- No, he's staring straight ahead.
- Straight ahead?

263
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:55,895
He's focused on his pacifier.

264
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:58,100
Yu Jun, you're not sleepy?

265
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,633
Yu Jun, we're going to a kids cafe.

266
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:06,266
Are you excited?

267
00:10:07,366 --> 00:10:10,533
(Where Yu Jun and the uncles
will play today)

268
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,100
I've never been to a kids cafe before.

269
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,466
I've been to a dog cafe, though.

270
00:10:15,466 --> 00:10:16,466
It's my first time too.

271
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,651
Has he ever been to one?

272
00:10:19,366 --> 00:10:20,600
He must have gone at least once.

273
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,100
(But never with the uncles!)

274
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:25,133
(Let's have a blast, Yu Jun.)

275
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:29,800
(Time to recharge before we start)

276
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,933
(They're fast asleep.)

277
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,800
(Sweet dreams.)

278
00:10:39,566 --> 00:10:43,233
(We can only imagine
how much fun he'll have.)

279
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:46,433
(Their first time at a kids cafe)

280
00:10:46,805 --> 00:10:49,700
- This way?
- There's a pool over here.

281
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,966
There's a pool, Yu Jun.

282
00:10:51,966 --> 00:10:53,033
(The place even has a swimming pool!)

283
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,400
Oh, wow.

284
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,458
- I didn't know they had areas like this.
- Oh, my.

285
00:10:59,066 --> 00:11:01,900
(Checking out the main pool
before heading in)

286
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,900
(Wary)

287
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:05,233
This is a shark.

288
00:11:07,466 --> 00:11:08,501
Not interested?

289
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,366
Yu Jun.

290
00:11:11,366 --> 00:11:12,733
- Look at this.
- What's this?

291
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,600
Could you take that out for me?

292
00:11:16,266 --> 00:11:17,933
Should I put it in his hand?

293
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,633
There you go.

294
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:23,633
(Yu Jun starts to show some interest.)

295
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:24,933
It's fun, right?

296
00:11:25,266 --> 00:11:26,152
He's stepping forward.

297
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,233
(Throw)

298
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:32,025
Yu Jun, you can go fishing. Look.

299
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,733
(Third time's the charm.)

300
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:38,133
If you like throwing things,
let's throw them.

301
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,100
(Strike one)

302
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,066
(Strike two)

303
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:45,033
(Strike out!)

304
00:11:45,133 --> 00:11:47,933
Yu Jun loves throwing.

305
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,770
He's excited
because there's so much to throw.

306
00:11:50,966 --> 00:11:52,245
Are you excited?

307
00:11:52,966 --> 00:11:54,400
(Getting splashed)

308
00:11:55,366 --> 00:11:59,233
(Supporting a future baseball star
isn't easy.)

309
00:11:59,466 --> 00:12:01,166
(I want that!)

310
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:02,166
Be careful.

311
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,366
(I'm going in.)

312
00:12:08,266 --> 00:12:09,133
(I want to go in.)

313
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:10,633
No.

314
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,000
Are you frustrated?

315
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,500
(He almost jumped in with his clothes on.)

316
00:12:14,866 --> 00:12:16,133
Hold on, Yu Jun.

317
00:12:16,133 --> 00:12:17,036
Let's go for a swim.

318
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,200
(Getting Yu Jun into his swimsuit)

319
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,633
(Grabbing on tight)

320
00:12:22,275 --> 00:12:23,776
Yu Jun, you look great.

321
00:12:24,883 --> 00:12:25,975
You look great, aren't you?

322
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,433
(Slipping his arm into the sleeve)

323
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,366
- You look so sharp.
- All done, Yu Jun.

324
00:12:29,366 --> 00:12:30,533
It looks good on you.

325
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:32,133
- Are these for us?
- Yes.

326
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:34,766
(The uncles put on waterproof aprons.)

327
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:35,766
Let's go.

328
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,233
Yu Jun, shall we go in?

329
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,333
(Splashing around after changing)

330
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:44,333
(Clapping like a seal)

331
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,600
(Yu Jun is getting used to the water.)

332
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,700
Throw it.

333
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,100
(Great job, sweetie.)

334
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:50,933
Good job.

335
00:12:51,566 --> 00:12:52,366
Hey.

336
00:12:53,233 --> 00:12:54,066
Choi Yu Jun.

337
00:12:54,066 --> 00:12:55,400
(Rocking the swimsuit)

338
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,000
Choi Yu Jun, get soaked!

339
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,400
(Take this!)

340
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,533
Get wet, Yu Jun!

341
00:13:01,233 --> 00:13:03,366
(Vocalizing)

342
00:13:03,766 --> 00:13:06,600
(A waterfall show for Yu Jun)

343
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,400
(He's not playing the shell game.)

344
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:10,933
(Let me make a waterfall too.)

345
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:14,000
(Lost in the water play)

346
00:13:14,266 --> 00:13:15,866
(He's so adorable.)

347
00:13:15,966 --> 00:13:16,800
Bump!

348
00:13:17,466 --> 00:13:18,266
Yu Jun.

349
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,433
Sunglasses.

350
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:22,466
(No!)

351
00:13:23,466 --> 00:13:24,900
Look at me.

352
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:26,300
Don't they look cool?
That's just his style.

353
00:13:27,066 --> 00:13:29,200
You'd look so cute if you tried them.

354
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,233
Do you want to try them on?

355
00:13:30,233 --> 00:13:32,500
(Putting the sunglasses back on Yu Jun)

356
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,166
(Is it a success?)

357
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:36,833
They're too big for his face.

358
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,500
He's crying.

359
00:13:38,733 --> 00:13:42,833
(Don't cry.)

360
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:45,100
(Thankfully, he stopped crying.)

361
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:47,700
Yu Jun.

362
00:13:47,725 --> 00:13:48,725
(Using every prop to keep him entertained)

363
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:50,700
It's me.

364
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:52,100
(Don't you want to wear them?)

365
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,966
(You look weird in those.)

366
00:13:54,966 --> 00:13:56,569
Good job. I didn't like them either.

367
00:13:56,933 --> 00:13:57,700
Hey.
Your turn.

368
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:00,966
(Strict about his own fashion style)

369
00:14:00,966 --> 00:14:02,100
That was a good attempt.

370
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:06,766
(Now Yu Jun is completely
used to the water.)

371
00:14:06,966 --> 00:14:08,733
Yu Jun, do you want to try a floatie?

372
00:14:08,733 --> 00:14:09,533
Shall we go?

373
00:14:13,629 --> 00:14:14,766
Do you want to play with SOOBIN?

374
00:14:14,766 --> 00:14:15,900
(He's finally in the main pool.)

375
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,833
- Yu Jun.
- It's a plane.

376
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:18,633
What is this?

377
00:14:20,066 --> 00:14:22,466
- Yu Jun.
- Do you want to get out? Wait.

378
00:14:22,466 --> 00:14:24,466
Yu Jun, here's Uncle BEOMGYU.

379
00:14:24,466 --> 00:14:26,600
Look. Uncle TAEHYUN is here too.

380
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,500
What's this?

381
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,633
(Thinking)

382
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:31,733
(Trying to grab his attention
with a melody waterfall)

383
00:14:31,966 --> 00:14:33,633
(Not a single smile)

384
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:34,600
What is this?

385
00:14:35,466 --> 00:14:36,633
He's a bit on edge.

386
00:14:38,266 --> 00:14:39,100
Is it not fun?

387
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,800
Look at the water falling.

388
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:41,800
(Fussing)

389
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:43,366
Look at this, Yu Jun.

390
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:46,100
(Pouting while holding his hand)

391
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,266
- Are you scared?
- What?

392
00:14:47,266 --> 00:14:49,033
This is the best part.
This is the highlight.

393
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:51,933
Yu Jun, look at this.

394
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,133
- The plane is coming out.
- Why are you crying?

395
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:55,033
Do you want me to pick you up?
(Sad)

396
00:14:55,831 --> 00:14:58,200
- You need to hold him.
- Okay, okay.

397
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,166
(Babies never like the main event.)

398
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:04,233
He's pouting because he's scared.

399
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,033
Shall we go?

400
00:15:06,366 --> 00:15:07,466
To the play area!

401
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:10,533
(Making up for the pool time
in the play area)

402
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:12,066
Yu Jun, what's this?

403
00:15:12,766 --> 00:15:13,933
It's a piano.

404
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:18,433
(Not interested)

405
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:20,800
Yu Jun.

406
00:15:22,366 --> 00:15:23,800
Yu Jun, shall we go down the slide?

407
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,333
He's heading for the stairs again.

408
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:27,233
He loves stairs.

409
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,833
- One.
- One. There you go.

410
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:31,166
(Yu Jun loves stairs!)

411
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:32,633
- Two.
- Two.

412
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,800
- Three.
- Three.

413
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,066
(Going up the stairs on all fours)

414
00:15:36,066 --> 00:15:37,200
Four.

415
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,166
In 1, 2, 3!

416
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:41,266
(He even goes down the slide with him.)

417
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:43,433
Gosh.

418
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:45,666
(Thanks to Airbag SOOBIN,
Yu Jun had a smooth ride.)

419
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:49,400
One more time?

420
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,666
- One, two.
- One, two.

421
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:54,166
- Three.
- Nice.

422
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:55,900
- Four.
- Good job.

423
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:56,900
(Lower and lower)

424
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:59,500
- Great job.
- Well done.

425
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,633
Here we go.

426
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,666
It's faster than I thought.

427
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:05,600
(Smiling)

428
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:11,566
(A big smile showing his bottom teeth)

429
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:14,166
Yu Jun, where are you going?
There's something over here.

430
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,000
You're right. There's a ball pit here.

431
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:19,000
(The ball pit is the heart
of a kids cafe.)

432
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,833
We have a ball pit here.

433
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,066
(Yu Jun, look at this.)

434
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:24,900
(Trying to get his attention)

435
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,000
(No reaction)

436
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:26,933
I'm the one getting excited.

437
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,300
Yu Jun, look.

438
00:16:28,325 --> 00:16:29,391
(Babies never do what they're told.)

439
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:30,500
(Turning around)

440
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:32,066
(I want to leave.)

441
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:33,500
Not interested?

442
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,566
This is so much fun.

443
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,300
- Don't you like it?
- It's so fun.

444
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,233
(I'm out.)

445
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:40,133
Where are you going?

446
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:41,566
Where to now?

447
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,000
You keep changing your mind.

448
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:44,966
(Exhausted)

449
00:16:45,275 --> 00:16:46,975
(Back to the stairs again)

450
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,200
(Take me upstairs)

451
00:16:49,566 --> 00:16:51,233
- Again?
- He really finds this fun.

452
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:52,578
Do you want to ride with me this time?

453
00:16:52,966 --> 00:16:55,166
(The YEONJUN Train is departing.)

454
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,500
Here we go.

455
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,000
(Sliding)
(Thud)

456
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,800
(Satisfied)

457
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,200
That really hurts your tailbone.

458
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,357
It's more painful than it looks.

459
00:17:04,966 --> 00:17:07,533
(I don't mind the pain
as long as Yu Jun is happy.)

460
00:17:07,533 --> 00:17:08,766
(In pain)

461
00:17:08,766 --> 00:17:09,700
Yu Jun, look over there.

462
00:17:10,326 --> 00:17:11,490
There's a playground.

463
00:17:11,529 --> 00:17:12,165
Yu Jun.

464
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:14,566
(I'm not going.)

465
00:17:15,766 --> 00:17:17,600
Yu Jun!

466
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,966
(Isn't this car fun?)

467
00:17:18,966 --> 00:17:20,400
There are so many cars here.

468
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,591
(A car that barks like a dog?)

469
00:17:22,466 --> 00:17:23,333
Yu Jun.

470
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,966
Yu Jun, look at this.

471
00:17:25,966 --> 00:17:28,033
(The uncles give it their all
to spark his interest.)

472
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,566
(Is Yu Jun finally reacting?)

473
00:17:31,566 --> 00:17:34,033
Yu Jun, let's dance.

474
00:17:34,266 --> 00:17:35,166
We're the only ones having fun.

475
00:17:35,166 --> 00:17:36,333
What was that? That scared me!

476
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,524
Yu Jun, do you want to ride in the car?

477
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:39,966
(Putting Yu Jun in the car)

478
00:17:39,966 --> 00:17:41,200
Yu Jun.

479
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,066
We didn't put his feet in.

480
00:17:42,066 --> 00:17:43,400
(Rejecting the car)

481
00:17:44,233 --> 00:17:45,000
This is...

482
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,766
(Back to the stairs)
Again?

483
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:51,704
There are so many other fun things
over there.

484
00:17:53,133 --> 00:17:54,166
Yu Jun, here we go.

485
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:57,033
(The departing signal sounds tired now.)

486
00:17:57,033 --> 00:17:58,633
(Groaning)

487
00:17:58,633 --> 00:17:59,733
Is it fun?

488
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,066
Is it really that fun?

489
00:18:01,566 --> 00:18:05,366
(He's finally done
with the stairs and the slide.)

490
00:18:09,266 --> 00:18:13,100
(Lunchtime, 12:30 p.m.)

491
00:18:14,766 --> 00:18:16,766
- That looks good.
- Yu Jun, time to eat!

492
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:19,733
(Here comes Yu Jun.)

493
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:21,100
(Skillfully placing Yu Jun
in the high chair)

494
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,033
Do you want to sit?

495
00:18:23,241 --> 00:18:26,322
- You choose.
- Truffle for sure.

496
00:18:26,353 --> 00:18:29,533
- Truffle risotto, definitely.
- And then...

497
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:31,733
(What about my food?)

498
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:33,733
(Feed me!)

499
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:36,400
(Give me water, at least.)

500
00:18:36,566 --> 00:18:37,800
- Do you want water?
- Do you want some water?

501
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,666
(Grabbing)

502
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:40,700
(He got thirsty from playing so hard.)

503
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:42,400
- He's drinking.
- He grabbed it right away.

504
00:18:43,366 --> 00:18:44,633
(Hydration level: 10 percent)

505
00:18:44,633 --> 00:18:45,900
(Hydration level: 20 percent)

506
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:46,900
Yu Jun.

507
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,333
Don't drink too fast.

508
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,100
(Hydration level: 50 percent)

509
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,133
He's going to finish the whole thing.

510
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:52,033
(A human sponge)

511
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:55,600
(Fascinated and worried)

512
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:56,466
Are you a Squirtle?

513
00:18:56,466 --> 00:18:59,300
They said he'll just keep drinking
until it's gone,

514
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:01,466
so I shouldn't give him too much.

515
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:03,166
Stop drinking for now.

516
00:19:03,166 --> 00:19:05,833
(Taking the water cup away)

517
00:19:06,233 --> 00:19:07,566
Drink a little more later.

518
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:08,966
You've had enough for now.

519
00:19:08,966 --> 00:19:11,366
(- Give me water!
- No)

520
00:19:11,766 --> 00:19:14,166
(YEONJUN gets a headbutt from Yu Jun)

521
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,400
Yu Jun.

522
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,966
(He won't miss this chance.)

523
00:19:17,266 --> 00:19:18,066
Yu Jun.

524
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,633
(Here you go.)

525
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:23,366
(Yu Jun is much more responsive
to affection now.)

526
00:19:23,366 --> 00:19:25,633
Nom-nom.

527
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:27,733
- Nom-nom?
- Nom-nom.

528
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:29,435
Should we ask them to heat up his food?

529
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:30,633
Are you hungry?

530
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:31,800
Even if it's served together...

531
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,133
(Ask them to heat up the baby food!)

532
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,800
I can press this, right?

533
00:19:36,366 --> 00:19:38,666
(Their food arrives at the perfect time.)

534
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:39,900
Excuse me.

535
00:19:40,266 --> 00:19:42,333
Could you heat up this baby food for us?

536
00:19:43,066 --> 00:19:46,200
It says "15 seconds in the microwave."

537
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,333
(The server happily obliges.)

538
00:19:48,533 --> 00:19:49,666
Thank you.

539
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,600
It looks amazing. This is crazy.

540
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,000
- It smells great.
- I'll handle that.

541
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,966
Yu Jun, sorry we're eating first.

542
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:59,066
- Sorry, buddy.
- Your food will be here soon.

543
00:19:59,066 --> 00:20:00,221
In less than a minute.

544
00:20:00,246 --> 00:20:01,646
We can put this in that, right?

545
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,400
Cool it before you give it to him.

546
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:04,866
Is it hot?

547
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,100
Not really.

548
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:10,800
(But let's cool it first,
just to be safe.)

549
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,300
This should be good, right?

550
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:14,400
(Double-checking the temperature)

551
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:16,266
It's totally fine.
Open up, Yu Jun!

552
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:20,933
He looks like he's enjoying it.

553
00:20:20,933 --> 00:20:22,100
(Yu Jun seems to love the food.)

554
00:20:22,633 --> 00:20:24,066
I'll do it. You can eat.

555
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:27,866
Here.

556
00:20:28,066 --> 00:20:31,666
(He cooled Yu Jun's food,
but forgot to cool his own.)

557
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:34,433
(But he didn't forget to cool
Yu Jun's food.)

558
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:35,233
Yu Jun!

559
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,933
(Opening his mouth)

560
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:37,800
(No!)

561
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,133
(I want to do it myself.)

562
00:20:39,633 --> 00:20:42,900
(I can eat fine by myself.)

563
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,133
I guess the food is good.

564
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,700
(Eating Uncle's hand)

565
00:20:46,566 --> 00:20:47,900
(Taking a bite)

566
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:50,066
That's my good boy!

567
00:20:50,866 --> 00:20:54,866
(Do you see your uncles eating well too?)

568
00:20:55,633 --> 00:20:58,600
(The three Chois are eating nonstop.)

569
00:20:59,033 --> 00:21:01,500
(Yu Jun and his uncles are
devouring their food.)

570
00:21:02,066 --> 00:21:03,100
It's so good.

571
00:21:03,466 --> 00:21:05,097
- What?
- It's so good.

572
00:21:05,122 --> 00:21:05,933
(Mine's good too.)

573
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:07,366
You're doing so well
at eating by yourself!

574
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,135
That might not be enough food.

575
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:10,500
We need one more pack.

576
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,433
(The Chois are starving
after playing in the water.)

577
00:21:13,259 --> 00:21:15,993
(A new mission: Ask the server
to heat the baby food once more.)

578
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:19,933
(Should I ask now? Or a bit later?
When should I ask?)

579
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:23,533
Could you please heat another one for us?

580
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:25,233
- And one more baby spoon?
- One more baby spoon?

581
00:21:26,266 --> 00:21:28,933
(They successfully asked
to heat another pack!)

582
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,023
You really love your food today,
don't you?

583
00:21:31,933 --> 00:21:33,000
You're eating so well today.

584
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,533
(Ready to eat his spoon)

585
00:21:34,966 --> 00:21:36,700
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

586
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,166
Thank you!

587
00:21:38,735 --> 00:21:39,900
(Preparing the second plate)

588
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,033
I'm scared it might be hot,

589
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:42,835
if he eats it right away.

590
00:21:43,166 --> 00:21:44,033
Hold on.

591
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:46,600
(Is it ready now?)

592
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,200
(I'm eating it, okay?)

593
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,790
Hold on.

594
00:21:49,814 --> 00:21:51,633
(I'll cool it for you.)

595
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:53,166
Thank you.

596
00:21:53,866 --> 00:21:54,800
That looks amazing.

597
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:59,900
(The Chois are onto their second round.)

598
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:06,266
(A dangerous video to watch late at night)

599
00:22:07,286 --> 00:22:08,833
(Watching the baby Choi
while chewing his food)

600
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,200
The pizza is so good.

601
00:22:10,566 --> 00:22:12,133
(My food is tasty too!)

602
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:13,900
(Nom)

603
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:16,936
Yu Jun, you're having a feast today!

604
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:23,633
(The uncles are having a feast too.)

605
00:22:24,766 --> 00:22:27,400
(The three Chois are starting
to look alike, even when they eat.)

606
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,914
That's a good boy!

607
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:30,800
Right on!

608
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:35,866
(After feasting for quite a while)

609
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:38,266
Gosh, Yu Jun.

610
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,000
Yu Jun!

611
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,600
(What's wrong?)

612
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,966
You've got food everywhere!

613
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,400
Here.

614
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,633
- You look awesome.
- Give me your hand.

615
00:22:47,633 --> 00:22:49,366
(Yu Jun now has a food beard.)

616
00:22:49,366 --> 00:22:51,770
It's like your mouth isn't
even on your face.

617
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:53,833
You spilled it everywhere.

618
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:55,900
But he almost finished it.

619
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:56,700
Yes, he did.

620
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,200
But he spilled half of it.

621
00:22:58,833 --> 00:23:02,233
(Uncle YEONJUN is cleaning
Yu Jun all day.)

622
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:04,266
(It's so tasty.)

623
00:23:04,666 --> 00:23:05,766
Do you want a snack?

624
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:07,466
- Is it good?
- The pizza is so good.

625
00:23:07,466 --> 00:23:08,900
- What?
- This pizza is the best.

626
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:09,800
Really?

627
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,100
(Let's see.)

628
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:14,333
(He's eating the whole thing in one bite.)

629
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:15,694
Did you eat it all at once?

630
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,700
(Give me one more.)

631
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,978
(No, maybe five more?)

632
00:23:21,833 --> 00:23:22,733
The rice crackers?

633
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:23,969
Should I give him one last piece?

634
00:23:27,566 --> 00:23:28,533
This is your last piece.

635
00:23:28,966 --> 00:23:29,933
Okay.

636
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:32,066
(The 15-month-old even knows
how to negotiate.)

637
00:23:34,466 --> 00:23:36,700
(Here!)

638
00:23:37,066 --> 00:23:38,800
(Yu Jun is showing affection first now!)

639
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:39,866
Are you sharing it with Uncle?

640
00:23:40,566 --> 00:23:41,566
What a good boy.

641
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,500
(He's looking for his mom.)

642
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,533
Mom?

643
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:48,466
I'm your mom from today.

644
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,400
Yu Jun.

645
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,733
I'm your mom from today.

646
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:53,166
(No!)

647
00:23:53,166 --> 00:23:55,733
(Yu Jun knows how to put his foot down.)

648
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:58,300
(Accepting his response right away)

649
00:23:58,766 --> 00:24:01,933
You were so popular at the kids cafe.

650
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:07,033
All the parents saw Yu Jun...

651
00:24:07,033 --> 00:24:08,533
and called him "the handsome boy."

652
00:24:09,066 --> 00:24:09,866
I know.

653
00:24:09,866 --> 00:24:12,300
You'll be so popular
once you start kindergarten.

654
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,366
Yu Jun is so pretty.

655
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,033
He's the prettiest.

656
00:24:16,033 --> 00:24:17,133
"Hello!"

657
00:24:17,733 --> 00:24:18,600
Bow!

658
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:19,966
"I love you!"

659
00:24:19,966 --> 00:24:22,200
(Hello. Oh, wait! I love you!)

660
00:24:23,166 --> 00:24:24,600
(They're done eating now.)

661
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,500
Let's go.

662
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:28,633
- Should we go?
- What?

663
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:29,533
"Should we go?"

664
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:30,970
Do you want to go home?

665
00:24:32,066 --> 00:24:34,400
(Heading home)

666
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:38,800
(Yu Jun and his uncles
passed out in the car.)

667
00:24:42,866 --> 00:24:46,533
(Sleeping soundly for 20 minutes)

668
00:24:48,468 --> 00:24:49,876
(A surprise mission:
taking him out of his seat)

669
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:51,233
- Press that.
- This?

670
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,126
I don't want to wake him.

671
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:58,433
(If they can get him out like this,
he can keep napping.)

672
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:03,733
(But YEONJUN's hands are feeling lost.)

673
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:08,000
(He couldn't get Yu Jun out
without waking him.)

674
00:25:11,533 --> 00:25:12,433
Sorry.

675
00:25:13,566 --> 00:25:14,766
Let's go home and sleep.

676
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,000
Let's get your pants changed first.

677
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,133
You peed a lot.

678
00:25:20,133 --> 00:25:22,533
- We need to get his shoes off first.
- He peed in his pants.

679
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:23,733
You're right.

680
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:24,933
(He's still drowsy and confused.)

681
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,533
Give me your foot.

682
00:25:27,066 --> 00:25:28,633
We need his shoes off before his pants.

683
00:25:29,266 --> 00:25:31,666
(I'm so sleepy.)

684
00:25:32,066 --> 00:25:34,500
(The golden window for a nap
is closing fast.)

685
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,366
Give me your sock.

686
00:25:35,733 --> 00:25:38,633
(Quickly changing his clothes and diaper)

687
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,700
Let's wash your hands and feet.

688
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:42,500
How do we wash him?

689
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:45,700
(Gosh!)
All done.

690
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:48,600
Hey.

691
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:52,766
I don't know what to do.
It's my first time.

692
00:25:52,766 --> 00:25:53,800
Let's start with his feet.

693
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:56,133
(YEONJUN is busy washing
Yu Jun's hands and feet.)

694
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:57,266
(Babbling)

695
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,933
(Babbling)

696
00:26:00,933 --> 00:26:02,433
Wait!

697
00:26:03,033 --> 00:26:04,933
Hold on!

698
00:26:04,933 --> 00:26:05,933
All done.

699
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:08,400
My back hurts.

700
00:26:09,266 --> 00:26:11,300
Yu Jun sleeps well with a pacifier.

701
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,966
(Taking the pacifier)

702
00:26:13,966 --> 00:26:15,900
(Yu Jun is ready for a nap)

703
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:22,300
(Yu Jun's first nap attempt at 2:20 p.m.)

704
00:26:22,633 --> 00:26:24,400
You need to pat his back...

705
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:27,600
while walking around
to help him drift off.

706
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,500
You have to pat him pretty firmly.

707
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:31,200
Yes, just like that.

708
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,033
Slowly.

709
00:26:32,666 --> 00:26:34,533
Walk around, and once he's out,

710
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:36,900
lay him on the bed.

711
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:37,800
Goodnight, Yu Jun.

712
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:39,600
Sleep tight.

713
00:26:40,666 --> 00:26:44,133
(YEONJUN has to put Yu Jun to bed alone.)

714
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:49,833
(SOOBIN gets a break from babysitting.)

715
00:26:50,966 --> 00:26:55,266
(YEONJUN follows
the nap master's instructions.)

716
00:26:57,733 --> 00:27:00,100
(But it's harder today
because his nap was interrupted.)

717
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:01,133
(Cranky)

718
00:27:01,133 --> 00:27:03,333
(Babbling)

719
00:27:05,166 --> 00:27:06,391
You can't sleep?

720
00:27:09,933 --> 00:27:18,466
(YEONJUN is singing a lullaby.)

721
00:27:24,833 --> 00:27:28,033
(He's leaning on YEONJUN now.)

722
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,733
(But he's also getting fussier.)

723
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:36,600
(Bursting into tears)

724
00:27:37,466 --> 00:27:39,800
(I'm so sad!)

725
00:27:41,433 --> 00:27:43,433
(Is Yu Jun crying?)

726
00:27:45,433 --> 00:27:47,100
(Will YEONJUN, the novice,)

727
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:50,228
(succeed in getting him to sleep?)
